"through the ingenuousness of her age beamed an ardent mind,
a mind not of the women but of the poet;
she did not please, she intoxicated"
— Alexandre Dumas

curious

words knocking at
the door soothe me
as quiet sounds bounce
off notes from left
to there
like seductive fog
as the distinctive
scent of your tone
arouses.

oh
 . . .
push back into me.
